        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 1:03AM CDT until June 8 at 1:45AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>SVRBMX

The National Weather Service in Birmingham has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northern Lamar County in west central Alabama...

* Until 145 AM CDT.

* At 103 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Sulligent,
moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Vernon, Sulligent, Detroit, Beaverton, Blooming Grove, Lamar County
Airport, Crews, Bedford, Henson Springs, and Pine Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
